<div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;">
<a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-HmhTBaMbb-8/UJftBitu1II/AAAAAAAAAAM/NTqVvOY1foY/s1600/153594c4goidl-9d6z6m-picture-21.png" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" height="231" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-HmhTBaMbb-8/UJftBitu1II/AAAAAAAAAAM/NTqVvOY1foY/s320/153594c4goidl-9d6z6m-picture-21.png" width="320" /></a></div>
<span style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">Using an apple computer for work makes no sense at all if for simple things we have to launch a virtual machine, for instance, the need to use Oracle SQL*Plus. Even if SQLDeveloper is now also available and provides a graphical interface, the fact that the way I deploy is mostly through scripts makes sql*plus mandatory in order to create and verify that they will work as expected. This is a quick guide on how to get sql*plus up and running on Mac OS X.</span></span><br />
<br />
<div class="section" id="author-section" style="border-bottom-color: rgb(51, 51, 51); border-bottom-style: dotted; border-bottom-width: 1px; margin-bottom: 2em; text-align: left;">
<h3 style="font-size: large;">
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">Obtaining the software</span></h3>
<div>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">Oracle provides versions for&nbsp;<a href="http://www.oracle.com/technology/software/tech/oci/instantclient/htdocs/macsoft.html">PPC</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="http://www.oracle.com/technology/software/tech/oci/instantclient/htdocs/intel_macsoft.html">Intel</a>&nbsp;(32 and 64 bits) based Mac OS X. For both cases, download the basic package (or the lite one for Intel) and the SQL*Plus package.</span></div>
<div>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"><br /></span></div>
<div>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">Uncompress the files, which will creates a folder named instantclient_10_2. Just for organization sake, move the folder to the Applications folder, rename it if you wish, just remember to use the new name instead of the original one in the following instructions.</span></div>
<div>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"><br /></span></div>
<h3 style="font-size: large;">
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">Configure environment variables</span></h3>
<div>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">Edit or create the .bash_profile file on your home directory</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<br /></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<span style="font-family: 'courier new', monospace;">cd</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<span style="font-family: 'courier new', monospace;">vi .bash_profile</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<br /></div>
<div>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">add the following lines:</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<br /></div>
<div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<span style="font-family: 'courier new', monospace;">DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=$DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH:/Applications/instantclient_10_2</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<span style="font-family: 'courier new', monospace;">export DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<span style="font-family: 'courier new', monospace;">TNS_ADMIN=/Applications/instantclient_10_2</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<span style="font-family: 'courier new', monospace;">export TNS_ADMIN</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<span style="font-family: 'courier new', monospace;">PATH=$PATH:/Applications/instantclient_10_2</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<span style="font-family: 'courier new', monospace;">export PATH</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<br /></div>
<div>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">First one, DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH is as per Oracle indication, to define access to dynamic libraries required for instant client. TNS_ADMIN, to identify location of TNS related configuration files and finally we add the instant client directory to the PATH in order to be able to execute sqlplus from the terminal no matter where in the file system we are located.</span></div>
<div>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"><br /></span></div>
<h4>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">Set up tnsnames entries</span></h4>
<div>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">Create the tnsnames.ora file under the $TNS_ADMIN directory and add the entries for the databases you need to access.</span></div>
<div>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;"><br /></span></div>
<h3 style="font-size: large;">
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">Execute sqlplus</span></h3>
<div>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">Either set up your environment variables from the current terminal window</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<br /></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<span style="font-family: 'courier new', monospace;">. ./.bash_profile</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<br /></div>
<div>
<span style="font-family: Verdana, sans-serif;">or open a new one, and then type&nbsp;</span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<br /></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<span style="font-family: 'courier new', monospace;">sqlplus /nolog</span></div>
</div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<span style="font-family: 'courier new', monospace;"><br /></span></div>
<div style="font-family: 'Gentium Book Basic', Georgia, serif;">
<span style="font-family: 'courier new', monospace;"><br /></span></div>
</div>
